re only paying for what you use and not one cent more.</li>\n</ul>',1501673881,NULL,1,0),(88,83,16,14,'In terms of their power to redefine the computing experience alone, workspaces bring with them a wide range of different benefits that cannot be ignored. Chief among them is the fact that they allow you to move away from the natural limitations of hardware into an era where any app can run on any machine, no exceptions.\n\nMany people believe that workspaces can currently only be enjoyed by large companies with even larger IT budgets, but this is absolutely not the case. In truth, there is no company too small for workspaces for a number of compelling reasons.\n\n![5981b9e6ae953.jpg](serve/attachment&path=5981b9e6ae953.jpg)  \n\n\nWorkspaces: A Great Fit for Smaller Companies\nOne of the major reasons why workspaces are a great option for smaller companies, in particular, is because they’re naturally more cost-effective than on-premise hardware. As IT environments get larger, you’re naturally dealing with a greater degree of complexity. This requires more service, more management, etc. With workspaces, you have none of these issues and get state-of-the-art technology in a sleek and sophisticated package.\n\nThey Shatter the Traditional Model\nIn many ways, larger businesses actually make more sense in terms of the traditional model of computing. Under the traditional model, companies have to purchase hardware and then replace it within 24 to 36 months. It’s a never-ending cycle of hardware replacement that requires a tremendous amount of money (and represents a major burden to small business owners in particular).\n\nYou’re also dealing with a never-ending performance lifecycle as well. One-year-old hardware isn’t as good as brand new hardware, requiring unending updates of software onto a platform that wasn’t designed to run newer versions of apps and programs in the first place. This causes the user experience to suffer, creating an environment that just gets worse and worse instead of getting better.\n\nWorkspaces, on the other hand, eliminate all of these concerns. You get a system that does exactly what you need when you need it from any location and you don’t have to worry about investing an additional dime into hardware as a result.\n\nThe Beauty of Workspaces is in Their Consistency\nFinally, one of the reasons why workspaces are terrific for small businesses, in particular, is because they offer a consistent, predictable experience for all users at all times. The back end hardware that you’re dealing with is so powerful that your end users will see almost no difference between this new model and the traditional model.\n\nFrom their perspective, nothing has changed. They can still do exactly what they need to on a daily basis, only now they can do it better than ever. From your perspective as a small business owner, everything has changed – for the better and for all time.\n\nIn the end, there is truly no company that is too small for the benefits that only workspaces can bring to the table. It’s such a powerful advancement that levels the technological playing field that we’re quickly moving towards an era where this is the only option. Small business owners around the world agree that this is very much a good thing.\n\nKey Takeaways:\n- There is truly no company that is so small that it couldn’t benefit from workspaces.\n- Workspaces will quickly not just eclipse the traditional model of computing, but replace it entirely.\n- End users see almost no differences between a workspace and a traditional computing model.','<p>In terms of their power to redefine the computing experience alone, workspaces bring with them a wide range of different benefits that cannot be ignored. Chief among them is the fact that they allow you to move away from the natural limitations of hardware into an era where any app can run on any machine, no exceptions.</p>\n<p>Many people believe that workspaces can currently only be enjoyed by larg